(3, '8-tips-to-crack-the-ibps-exam', '8 Tips to Crack The IBPS Exam', '<p>Under the administration of the Institute of Banking Personnel Selection (IBPS), a Mumbai based human resource agency, the entire employment program of the Indian banking sector is conducted. IBPS conducts employee recruitment exams for nationalized banks, Regional Rural Banks (RRBs), central and other financial institutions, cooperative banks, insurance companies, academic institutes, state-owned companies, and private corporates. The pattern of IBPS exams differs from each other slightly. However, the basic syllabus and structure of all IBPS exams are the same - beginning with the Common Written Exam (CWE) exam, followed by group discussion and personal interview respectively. In the case of, IBPS Clerk &amp; PO exam there are two rounds - Preliminary and Mains exam where those qualifying the Prelims are only eligible for mains exam and then interview.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is stating 8 simple tips that you can consider when in a plan to apply for any of the IBPS exams. Note, all IBPS exam preparation requires ample preparation and dedication to be cracked with a good score.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interview round of IBPS exam-&nbsp;</strong>In the interview round of the IBPS exam, you will be questioned by a panel of 3-4 professionals who will start from basic introductory questions, move to bank-specific questions and general knowledge arena. The total time range is less than half an hour per IBPS candidate and confidence is the chief key to crack the IBPS interview round.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Location of IBPS interview -</strong>&nbsp;Once you are confirmed an interview session for IBPS exam, make sure you gather enough information about the test center and reach there on time, on the exam day. Usually, IBPS interviews are held in their various departments across 200 locations in India.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Solving IBPS Reasoning section-</strong>&nbsp;The IBPS reasoning section aims to judge the rational and thinking capability of the test taker. The reasoning section contains 35 marks. However, to solve the IBPS reasoning section do not rely alone on your intelligence. Each question is backed by formulas or strategic approach. If you can pick the right option to solve an IBPS reasoning question, you are sure to get the final correct answer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Negative marking in IBPS exam-</strong>&nbsp;For every wrong answer, 0.25 mark is deducted from your total score. Therefore, do not answer in the IBPS exam just to complete the paper. Answer or attempt questions that you are sure about. Multiple wrong answers can hamper your score. Hence, it&#39;s better to only answer questions in the IBPS exam that you are confident about.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Solve previous year IBPS question papers-</strong>&nbsp;Alike any other entrance exam, the suggestion of solving old question papers extends to the IBPS exam as well. Many remain confused for changing syllabus patterns, whether to solve old papers. Despite syllabus change, experts recommend solving IBPS old papers to master the strategic approach of solving IBPS paper in time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Special area to cover for IBPS exam-</strong>&nbsp;While the entire exam procedure to the syllabus of the IBPS exam might be like any other entrance exam, the only distinguishing point is - the IBPS exam requires focusing on the Indian economy and banking sector. Every IBPS aspirant should have a clear idea about Indian banks, their work system, history, and related stories in order to acquire a job in this field.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Computer knowledge</strong>&nbsp;As Indian banks are still on the process of going completely electronic/online, every IBPS candidate now needs to have clear computer knowledge. For the computer paper, you should definitely cover the following topics during IBPS exam preparation - Basic of Computers, Operating System Functions, Basic internet knowledge and protocols, Computer Basic Questions, Network basics (LAN &amp; WAN), Generations of the computer, Input &amp; Output Device, Shortcuts &amp; Basic of MS office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>IBPS Learning Strategy</strong>&nbsp;As the IBPS exam includes different kinds of subjects, some students plan to learn each subject one by one. This strategy is time-consuming and may make you forget GK when you are preparing maths. The remedy here is, to pay equal focus to all subjects you plan to cover. Solving some maths in the morning, learning GK in the evening and ending with the computer is a good day during your IBPS exam preparation stage.</p>', '', 'Vibrant Career', '2020-03-29'),
(5, 'media', 'Media', '<p><strong>W</strong>e are blessed to be the citizen of the biggest democratic setup where imposition is completely forbidden. Democracy acknowledges once worthiness and renders opportunities to contribute accordingly to flourish oneself and the nation. The settlement of fractions through the exchange of opinions is also an important trait of democracy. In a democracy, acceptance of the views cannot be subjected to forcefulness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Media provides a platform where diversified opinions can be expressed dauntlessly which can further be transformed into acceptability. Democracy seeks diligence and its beneficiaries should be so adequately educated that they can put forth their viewpoint assertively and be able to criticize the measures taken by their government or against any malpractice. Education provides prudent leaders and along with it, media can intellectually propagate knowledge and information. The media should comment, appreciate and criticize the steps taken by the government. Media feed the public mind to make them have an unbiased perception which affects society at large. So media, in any form, helps extend public opinion which develops a robust relationship between the government and common mass. It familiarises students, the future of any country, with government policies and its principles. It also performs as an institute as it inculcates awareness among the public and educated them in another way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Media coverage that lacks research and facts can create chaos and turmoil though it is meant to mitigate both. Media should be impartial in reporting and should not be biased towards or against a particular government, opinion, community, principal, etc. It is expected to form a positive public opinion through intertwining the news with the collection of facts and researches.</p>', './assets/uploads/728887e3dd666e93e1421eb14e064c7f.jpg', 'Vibrant Career', '2020-03-30'),
(6, 'forgiveness', 'Forgiveness', '<p><strong>F</strong>orgiveness is often acknowledged as a sign of cowardice, on the contrary, it is an act of courage hence needs plaudits. Not all the mortal beings endowed with the trait of forgiveness but mankind though it is not easy for all to learn that. One may excel it with a perpetual practice. Forgive and forget attitude mitigates the mind&rsquo;s engagement from eternal vindictiveness and taint one&#39;s impressionable control unit which can otherwise be used in promising brainchild.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>An ultimate goal of a hermit&rsquo;s penance is to acquire divine interface between him and the Almighty but any wrongful act of a layman against him may instigate his spiteful persona. Can the ripples so caused allow him to remain engrossed in cherishing his objective? One&rsquo;s only objective is to avenge makes him the most perilous whose company is never recommended.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our brain is built to radiate creativity. If one engages it not in taking revenge it would render a lot of creative ideas. But at the same time, it is clogged to create ideas for one&rsquo;s real goal if engaged in malicious activities and if it is forced the results will not be other&rsquo;s fault. For those consequences, the brain cannot be blamed either because this is how we had harnessed it.</p>', './assets/uploads/04f37aed345a5118cff1ce360d277296.jpg', 'Vibrant Career', '2020-03-30'),
(7, 'everything-is-destined-to-be-normal', 'Everything is destined to be normal ...', '<p>It is not at all justifiable to say that we are not panicking. Agencies have been contending with various problems followed by covid-19. We have been waiting desperately to see a steep declining curve in the number of corona cases on the dashboard. the worst hits are opulent Europe, USA and Britain. The corona cases are&nbsp;inching around our vicinity too.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWhat is elevating our fear? The news which is hammering through television &nbsp;and social media prompted us to start feeling as if it is all happening just outside our doors. All these news include increasing corona cases, economic uncertainty, attack on agency workers, extension of lock-down spree, job loss, corona affected patients are at large and many more. Further everyone is apprehensive about their stalled routine and dreams.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is easier said than done but we have Hobson&#39;s choice of observing optimism. Restrain yourself listening to the news frequently from any medium. Do the activities which inculcate the feeling of well being. We can only control the situation which is beyond our control by controlling our own wits. Give yourself ninety seconds when you are super stressed to still your mind from wild flights.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We do have different preferences to remain tranquil. These include workout, prayer, meditation, positive chats with optimistic people and all. Everything has energy and is vibrating at different frequencies. It is very significant to keep a high frequency environment physically, mentally and emotionally positive to get rid of discouraging thoughts. Never let your fear suppress you. Never succumb to fear. Watch the news in brief once a day that too from reliable sources. High vibrations boost our immunity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have a deep breath and utter &quot;I am healthy, I am ammune to every disease and I am safe&quot;. Nothing is in our control but fortify our homes, cover nose and mouth with recommended mask or piece of cloth, maintain physical distance, carry hand sanitizer while dealing outside home, keep the currency change in a polyethylene in vehicle itself.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Studies, jobs, exams, money can hardly be the substitute of life. All these &nbsp;can be repossessed till the beings remain animate. Have a strong belief that after a while everything is destined to be normal or will take some time to become normal. We are there not to lose any hope and follow all possible scientific methods to keep the virus off. Introspect positively.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Believe, life will guffaw again, lanes will be filled with people again, will be meeting with&nbsp;our loved ones again, we will be engrossed in our busy schedule and will fall short of time again, we all will be together again, we will be together again.</p>', './assets/uploads/f816f5151895617263a1796f4fc3ecfd.jpg', 'Vijay Sir', '2020-04-19');

